Overview
This project is a web-based stopwatch application that allows users to start, stop, and reset a timer. The application is built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, providing a simple and intuitive user interface.

Features
Start/Stop Functionality: Start and stop the timer with a single button.
Reset Functionality: Reset the timer to zero.
Responsive Design: The application adapts to various screen sizes and devices.
Lap Times (Optional): Record and display lap times.
Technologies Used
HTML5: For the structure of the web page.
CSS3: For styling the application.
JavaScript: For the stopwatch functionality and user interactions.
HTML
The index.html file contains the structure of the web page, including the stopwatch display and control buttons.

CSS
The styles.css file includes the following:

Base Styles: Basic styling for body, headings, buttons, etc.
Layout: Flexbox layout for centering the stopwatch and buttons.
Responsive Design: Media queries to adjust the layout for different screen sizes.
JavaScript
The script.js file includes:

Stopwatch Logic: JavaScript functions to handle starting, stopping, and resetting the timer.
Event Listeners: JavaScript to manage button clicks for controlling the stopwatch.
